chunk_content: In some oUs and SNUs, this may require implementing partners to compare their program cohorts to determine under which OVC_SERV program model disaggregate an individual should be counted. Example scenarios are below: • A 14-year-old girl is enrolled in the OVC Comprehensive Program, is an active DREAMS participant, and has completed an approved primary prevention of HIV and sexual violence intervention. She should be reported exclusively in the “OVC Comprehensive” disaggregate by the partner implementing the OVC Comprehensive program. The partners who serve her in the OVC Preventive or DREAMS program should not report her under OVC_SERV. • A 10-year-old boy is enrolled in the OVC Comprehensive Program. Additionally, he completes an approved primary prevention of HIV and sexual violence intervention. He should be reported exclusively under the “OVC Comprehensive” disaggregate.
